---
source: crates/audiomirror-cli/tests/help_snapshots.rs
expression: output
---
Listen for incoming UDP Opus packets on the given bind address and
play decoded audio on the specified output device. Runs until interrupted (Ctrl-C).

An adaptive jitter buffer absorbs packet reordering and network jitter. Use
--jitter-mode min for lowest-latency monitoring, or leave it as auto (default) for
robust delivery over congested LANs.

Examples:
audiomirror-cli recv --output "Built-in Speakers" --bind 0.0.0.0:5004

# Minimum latency mode
audiomirror-cli recv --output "Headphones" --bind 0.0.0.0:5004 --jitter-mode min

Usage: audiomirror-cli recv [OPTIONS] --output <OUTPUT> --bind <BIND>

Options:
      --output <OUTPUT>
          

      --bind <BIND>
          

      --jitter-mode <JITTER_MODE>
          [default: auto]
          [possible values: auto, min]

      --jitter-max-depth-ms <JITTER_MAX_DEPTH_MS>
          [default: 100]

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
